abstract: Brooklyn prosecutors will move to dismiss rape charges against five teenagers accused of assaulting woman in Brownsville neighborhood playground in January, citing conflicting accounts provided by woman and her father, as well as fact that she is unwilling to testify or cooperate further with investigation.

headline.print_headline: Prosecutors Will Move to Dismiss Charges in Playground Rape Case
headline.main: Prosecutors Will Move to Dismiss Charges in Brownsville Rape Case

snippet: The effort to drop the case against five teenagers accused of attacking an 18-year-old woman came primarily as the victim’s credibility as a witness fell apart, officials said.
lead_paragraph: The effort to drop the case against five teenagers accused of attacking an 18-year-old woman came primarily as the victim’s credibility as a witness fell apart, officials said.
